Checking outliers

Out[23]:
<Axes: >
  • We find the presence of outliers from the box plot displayed above shown. So, we need to treat the outliers.
In[24]:
def detect_outliers_zscore(data):
    threshold = 3
    mean = np.mean(data)
    std = np.std(data)
    outliers = []
    for i in data:
        z_score = (i - mean) / std
        if np.abs(z_score) > threshold:
            outliers.append(i)
    return outliers

sample = [15, 101, 18, 7, 13, 16, 11, 21, 5, 15, 10, 9]
sample_outliers = detect_outliers_zscore(sample)

#log transformation
df['Reviews'] = np.log1p(df['Reviews'])  # Add 1 before taking the log

def convert_size(Size):
    try:
        if 'million'in Size:
            return float(Size.replace('million',''))*1000000
        elif 'thousand' in Size:
            return float(Size.replace('thousand',''))*1000
        else:
            return float(Size)
    except ValueError:
        return None
df['Size'] = df['Size'].apply(convert_size)
